'''[[muffin]] [[cap]]'''

#A style of close-fitting [[cap]] or [[hat]] worn by women in the [[16th century]] and later; a [[caul]].
#A low, loose cap resembling a [[beret]], but with a [[brim]] that goes all the way around the head; [[popularize]]d in the [[19th century]] as a hat for [[children]], especially in the [[lower classes]].

